# Hermes Desktop Organization — gitignore
# --------------------------------------
# Only track the documentation layer. Bulk binary content stays local.

# The actual files I do want to commit
!README.md
!CONSOLIDATION_REPORT.md
!MANIFEST.csv
!consolidate.sh
!build_report.py
!.gitignore

# Everything else (binary trees) is ignored
/*
!/README.md
!/CONSOLIDATION_REPORT.md
!/MANIFEST.csv
!/consolidate.sh
!/build_report.py
!/.gitignore

# But explicitly re-allow the docs at the root (already allowed above)

# Don't ignore macOS noise inside the docs layer
.DS_Store
*.swp
*.tmp

# If you ever want to commit a small sample of each category, do it explicitly:
# !Media/Images/.gitkeep